    ```javascript
function rootSumEqual(root) {
    if (!root) return false;
    return (root.val === root.left.val + root.right.val);
}
```


    The algorithm checks if the given root node exists, and if it does, it checks whether the value of the root is equal to the sum of the values of its left and right children. If the root does not exist, it returns false. This works for a tree consisting of exactly 3 nodes as specified in the question.

